Elgeyo Marakwet secondary school head teachers have been warned against involving themselves in the purchase of school uniform.  County education director Joseph Wamocho said the school heads will be monitored to ensure parents are not asked to buy uniforms at high prices from certain suppliers handpicked by principals. Read : Parents warn schools against illegal fees, praise Matiang'i for reforms He said yesterday parents should be allowed to buy uniform from suppliers of their choice. “Don’t ask students to pay any fee for school uniforms. Principals should refrain from involvement in uniforms.  Purchase of uniforms should be dictated by market prices,” Wamocho said.  The education boss said security agencies have been deployed to monitor and possibly arrest those involved in the uniform purchase racket.  “Security agencies will be on high alert to ensure parents are not exploited when buying uniforms,” he said. Click here for the latest political news